</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEA9211FE102FDCFDD76386" bold="true" box="[483,563,2003,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="585">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26A57F4FFEA9211FE102FDCFDD76386" box="[483,563,2003,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="585" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
male.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFEB9210FF642899FB3D65C0" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEB9210FF642899FECD64DD" bold="true" box="[151,297,150,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Head: round and almost as wide as the pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13162A18FFEB9210FC432898FBEE64DC" box="[944,1034,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,846,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-282@3.[264,1323,846,1771]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Fodigryllus bisetus sp. nov. A, dorsal view of male; B, head in frontal view of male; C, anal plate (Scale bar= 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457451" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457451/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); occiput round and convex, frontal rostrum almost twice wider than the antennal scape; eyes large but not convex, three ocelli disposed as triangle, lateral ocelli large and vertically oval, median ocelli smaller (
<figureCitation id="13162A18FFEB9210FCA328D0FC4C6494" box="[848,936,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,846,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-282@3.[264,1323,846,1771]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Fodigryllus bisetus sp. nov. A, dorsal view of male; B, head in frontal view of male; C, anal plate (Scale bar= 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457451" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457451/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); maxillary palps with distal three segments elongated and fifth segment widened. Thorax: pronotum pubescent, slightly wider than length; forewing short with 3 oblique veins; mirror rounded and flattened with dividing vein not conspicuous; apical field nearly absent; external tympanum large and ovoid, internal tympanum absent (
<figureCitation id="13162A18FFEB9210FCAD2944FC386508" box="[862,988,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,734,758]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,181,710]" captionTargetId="figure-20@4.[264,1323,181,710]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Fodigryllus bisetus sp. nov. A, foretibia from outer side; B, foretibia from inner side; C, foretibiae from front side (Scale bar= 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457455/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
); two long hairs on each foretibia, one extended outwards and one extended forwards (
<figureCitation id="13162A18FFEB9210FD422960FCEE65E4" box="[689,778,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,734,758]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,181,710]" captionTargetId="figure-20@4.[264,1323,181,710]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Fodigryllus bisetus sp. nov. A, foretibia from outer side; B, foretibia from inner side; C, foretibiae from front side (Scale bar= 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457455" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457455/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia slightly shorter than hind femur, armed with 4 pairs of dorsal spurs; anal plate concave in the base (
<figureCitation id="13162A18FFEB9210FD16299CFCD965C0" box="[741,829,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,846,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-282@3.[264,1323,846,1771]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Fodigryllus bisetus sp. nov. A, dorsal view of male; B, head in frontal view of male; C, anal plate (Scale bar= 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457451" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457451/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); cercus little shorter than hind tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFEB9210FF6429B8FCF46598" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">
Genitalia: Epiphallus possessing a notch in middle, the lateral lobes of epiphallus curved inwards and upwards, and narrower than ectoparamere in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13162A18FFEB9210FD7B29D4FCE06598" box="[648,772,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1351,1375]" captionTargetBox="[311,1302,819,1308]" captionTargetId="figure-51@4.[286,1302,819,1327]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5. Fodigryllus bisetus sp. nov. A, genitalia in dorsal view; B, ventral view; C, lateral view (Scale bar= 0.5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457457/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Fig. 5A–C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFEB9210FF3429F0FE466674" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,825]" box="[199,418,511,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEB9210FF3429F0FEC16674" bold="true" box="[199,293,511,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFEB9210FF342A2DFB6B6650" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,825]" box="[199,1167,546,573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEB9210FF342A2DFEAB6651" bold="true" box="[199,335,546,572]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body uniformly black with the base of hind tibiae reddish brown (
<figureCitation id="13162A18FFEB9210FBCF2A2CFB656650" box="[1084,1153,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,2003,2027]" captionTargetId="figure-135@2.[350,1238,1607,1977]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Fodigryllus bisetus sp. nov. male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6458252" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6458252/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFEB9210FF342A48FCD466E8" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEB9210FF342A48FE0E660D" bold="true" box="[199,490,582,609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Measurements (in mm).</emphasis>
Male: body length (from head to anus) 16.59–16.90, pronotum length 3.22–3.93, forewing length 9.26–9.68, hind femur length 11.57–12.13.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3376516FFEB9210FF342A81FD636778" pageId="3" pageNumber="586" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFEB9210FF342A81FDC566C4" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,825]" box="[199,545,654,681]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEB9210FF342A81FE8566C5" bold="true" box="[199,353,654,680]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F33A760DFFEB9210FE942A80FE4E66C4" box="[359,426,655,681]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49E9F87FFFEB9210FE4A2A80FDF166C4" box="[441,533,655,681]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFEB9210FF342ABCFD636778" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEB9210FF342ABCFE6166A1" bold="true" box="[199,389,690,717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Natural history.</emphasis>
This species digs tunnels on slopes beside a road, and males sing near the entrance at night as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFEB9210FF642AD8FED1669C" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="1983" box="[151,309,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Tarbinskiellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEB9210FF642AD8FED1669C" box="[151,309,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Tarbinskiellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFEB9210FE992AD8FD8C669C" box="[362,616,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Gymnogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEB9210FE992AD8FDED669C" box="[362,521,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Gymnogryllus</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
The hole is as broad as the specimen’s size, and two hairs probably touch the wall of its tunnel for detecting vibration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3376516FFEB9210FF342B10FB8F6754" box="[199,1131,799,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFEB9210FF342B10FB8F6754" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,825]" box="[199,1131,799,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEB9210FF342B10FEAA6754" bold="true" box="[199,334,799,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFEB9210FDD12B10FD946754" authorityName="Liu &amp; He" authorityYear="2022" box="[546,624,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Fodigryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bisetus">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEB9210FDD12B10FD946754" box="[546,624,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="586">bisetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to two filiform hairs on each foretibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
